This paper discusses the design, development, and deployment of systems for anonymous communication, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the routing characteristics of different anonymous communication protocols, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the privacy implications of these protocols, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
